input.command:
ghx run pr.reviews.submit --input - <<'EOF'
{
  "owner": "aryeko",
  "name": "ghx-bench-fixtures",
  "prNumber": 445,
  "event": "REQUEST_CHANGES",
  "body": "Requesting changes based on review run run_1772555729706. I found multiple blocking issues in `src/utils/helpers.ts`: (1) the `fs` import has a typo (`improt`) and will fail compilation, (2) `divide` always divides by zero (`a / 0`) instead of using `b`, which returns incorrect values/Infinity and masks caller errors, and (3) `waitForReady` is an infinite busy-loop that never exits and can peg a CPU core. Please fix these and add tests to cover normal/error behavior for `divide` and a bounded/non-blocking readiness wait strategy.",
  "comments": [
    {
      "path": "src/utils/helpers.ts",
      "line": 2,
      "side": "RIGHT",
      "body": "`improt` is a typo and causes a syntax/compile failure. Replace with `import { readFileSync } from \"fs\"` so the module can build."
    },
    {
      "path": "src/utils/helpers.ts",
      "line": 8,
      "side": "RIGHT",
      "body": "This is a functional bug: `divide` ignores `b` and always divides by zero. Use `a / b` and handle `b === 0` explicitly (throw or return a well-defined error) so callers don't get silent `Infinity`/`-Infinity`."
    },
    {
      "path": "src/utils/helpers.ts",
      "line": 12,
      "side": "RIGHT",
      "body": "`while (true)` here creates an unbounded busy wait that never yields and can consume 100% CPU indefinitely. Replace with an async/polling mechanism with timeout/cancellation, or block on an actual readiness signal."
    }
  ]
}
EOF

